      "id": "yYFvPkWMGeTSJhccrmjgy2xukftckrep",
      "questionNumber": 1,
      "questionText": "Which of the following compounds shows\ngeometrical isomerism?",
      "options": [
        "2-methylpent-1-ene",
        "4-methylpent-1-ene",
        "2-methylpent-2-ene",
        "4-methylpent-2-ene"
      ],
      "correctOption": 3,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "isomerism",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Only 4-methylpent-2-ene shows geometrical isomerism.</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l4050fdd/951e35ae-2abb-4199-be2d-7ea23148df89/14fe4410-e42a-11ec-bb34-53a172f47ddb/file-1l4050fde.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l4050fdd/951e35ae-2abb-4199-be2d-7ea23148df89/14fe4410-e42a-11ec-bb34-53a172f47ddb/file-1l4050fde.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2020 (Online) 6th September Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 206 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l4051l28/a20db963-a81f-4e04-a584-cb34d22f40d9/3532e510-e42a-11ec-8caf-67af7033108e/file-1l4051l29.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l4051l28/a20db963-a81f-4e04-a584-cb34d22f40d9/3532e510-e42a-11ec-8caf-67af7033108e/file-1l4051l29.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2020 (Online) 6th September Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 206 English Explanation 2\">",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "1lgp2yz2n",
      "questionNumber": 2,
      "questionText": "<p>Given below are two statements :</p>\n<p>Statement I : Tropolone is an aromatic compound and has $$8 \\pi$$ electrons.</p>\n<p>Statement II : $$\\pi$$ electrons of $$ > \\mathrm{C}=\\mathrm{O}$$ group in tropolone is involved in aromaticity.</p>\n<p>In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below:</p>",
      "options": [
        "Statement I is false but Statement II is true",
        "Both Statement I and Statement II are false",
        "Statement I is true but Statement II is false",
        "Both Statement I and Statement II are true"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "aromaticity",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Statement I: A cyclic compound is aromatic only when it follows Hückel’s rule, i.e., it must have $$(4n+2)\\pi e^-$$ in a continuous, cyclic, conjugated system.</p>\n<p>If a ring has $8\\pi$ electrons, then $8 = 4n$ (with $n=2$), which fits the $4n$ type. Such a system is not aromatic (it is antiaromatic if it is fully planar and fully conjugated). So, saying “tropolone is aromatic and has $8\\pi$ electrons” is incorrect.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1momts88x/4216eb9e-702d-479f-8496-397215f92a31/50c08310-4550-11f1-b3bf-274115fadc91/file-jaoe38c1momts88y.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1momts88x/4216eb9e-702d-479f-8496-397215f92a31/50c08310-4550-11f1-b3bf-274115fadc91/file-jaoe38c1momts88y.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 13th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 131 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Aromatic as per Huckel rule i.e. $(4 n+2) \\pi e^{-}$.</p>\n<p>So, Statement I is worng.</p>\n<p>Statement II: In the $&gt;\\mathrm{C}=\\mathrm{O}$ (carbonyl) group, the $\\pi$ electrons are mainly involved in the C=O bond itself.</p>\n<p>These $\\pi$ electrons do not become part of the ring’s continuous cyclic conjugation (the cyclic $\\pi$-electron cloud needed for aromaticity). Therefore, they are not counted as the ring $\\pi$ electrons responsible for aromaticity.</p>\n<p>So, Statement II is also incorrect.</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "mnsik78m",
      "questionNumber": 3,
      "questionText": "<p>$$ \\text { The total number of aromatic compounds/species from the following is } $$</p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 8th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 9 English\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mnsj7lk7/39877958-dbcb-4d6c-a048-c643869dea85/74452f70-34a7-11f1-8461-75c223c4ecce/file-6y3zli1mnsj7lk8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mnsj7lk7/39877958-dbcb-4d6c-a048-c643869dea85/74452f70-34a7-11f1-8461-75c223c4ecce/file-6y3zli1mnsj7lk8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\">",
      "options": [
        "<p>6</p>",
        "<p>4</p>",
        "<p>3</p>",
        "<p>5</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "aromaticity",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Aromatic compounds are planar, cyclic and completely conjugated systems. They follow $(4 n+2) \\pi e^-$ rule called Huckel rule.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 8th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 9 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mo4ilus5/0eadcd5a-8c88-4646-ab96-f7450c3739ec/7f62ab60-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4ilus6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mo4ilus5/0eadcd5a-8c88-4646-ab96-f7450c3739ec/7f62ab60-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4ilus6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 8th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 9 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mo4ilvrt/e0c1f449-3ed0-491a-9847-91c2fbe7fdbc/80267090-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4ilvru.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mo4ilvrt/e0c1f449-3ed0-491a-9847-91c2fbe7fdbc/80267090-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4ilvru.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 8th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 9 English Explanation 3\" src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mo4ilwes/132b5865-0675-43dd-a78b-38ce05d388d4/80a4a140-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4ilwet.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mo4ilwes/132b5865-0675-43dd-a78b-38ce05d388d4/80a4a140-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4ilwet.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>",
      "section": "A",
