      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "electron-displacement-effect",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "In aromatic\nelectrophilic substitution reaction, electrofile attacks to the ring whose electron density is more.\n<picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7km5fk03kxkg3/38783c01-719e-4b3b-b721-3a1e89651665/0a585130-ce26-11e9-acf6-6d09a288f7f2/file-7km5fk03kxkg4-320w.jpg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7km5fk03kxkg3/38783c01-719e-4b3b-b721-3a1e89651665/0a585130-ce26-11e9-acf6-6d09a288f7f2/file-7km5fk03kxkg4-500w.jpg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 680px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7km5fk03kxkg3/38783c01-719e-4b3b-b721-3a1e89651665/0a585130-ce26-11e9-acf6-6d09a288f7f2/file-7km5fk03kxkg4-680w.jpg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/7km5fk03kxkg3/38783c01-719e-4b3b-b721-3a1e89651665/0a585130-ce26-11e9-acf6-6d09a288f7f2/file-7km5fk03kxkg4-860w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 9th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 227 English Explanation\"></picture>\n<br><br><b>Note :</b> -M effect is more powerful than  -I effect, that is why electron density will be less in the ring for  -M effect.",
